        <updateDate>2022-11-10T16:30:01Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Strategic Production Response Act or the SPR Act</b></p> <p>This bill limits the drawdown of petroleum in the Strategic Petroleum Reserve until the Department of Interior issues a plan or updates a previously issued plan to increase the production of oil and gas on federal land. The bill defines <i>federal land</i> to (1) include Outer Continental Shelf land; and (2) exclude land otherwise not available for oil and gas development within the National Park System, the National Wildlife Refuge System, the National Wilderness Preservation System, a National Marine Sanctuary, or Indian land.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
